Former Kaduna Central senator, Shehu Sani has mocked the President Muhammadu Buhari government over its penchant for holding security meetings behind closed doors. Sani took to his twitter handle, @ShehuSani on Thursday to argue that since nothing has changed in terms of the security situation in the country despite the several closed door meetings between the president and security chiefs, it was time to also close the windows. “Security Meeting behind close doors,nothing changes,” Sani wrote. “May be you need to also close the Windows.” President Buhari had earlier on Thursday, received security briefing from the country’s security chiefs at the presidential villa behind closed doors